Soren <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artillis>Artillis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Enjoys Sheep Erotica</span><br>  Posts: 1871<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 10:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New changes on test</span><hr size=1> Now all they need to do is give every magic item of any value a apropriate level requirement and the low end would be fun again.<br>
<br>
To those that don't agree with me I've done my share of tweeking but even if you have the gear on your character for the moment they get the level its more fun to work for those levels and work with people to get them.<br>
<br>
I have a tweek frog cleric that I geared for pure melle, Frog has silver chiten hand wraps and a Goranga spiked club and decent armor.  Combine that with there healing spells there sooth spells for single pulling and yalp and cleric buffs and I was solo clearing all of bandit camp one in paludal and tanking multiple dark blues at once.  Only buff I had that was not cast by me was KEI (which does of course make a differance).<br>
<br>
But come on a cleric of all things tanking better then some twinked melles that were near me all because I could heal myself as needed and was probably hitting as good as a paladin at my level.  I had zero down time thanks to KEI.  Even clerics don't have to group at low levels to gain fast easy exp.  My cleric gains faster exp solo then then they'd ever get grouped but not quite as fast as my wizard was getting quad kitting at the low 20's. <br>
<br>
So on that note i think all items need a level limit except non magic stuff like fine steal and non magical player made armor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=filanfyretracker>Filan Fyretracker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1928<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 10:16 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New changes on test</span><hr size=1> guess their nerfing the old PL system.  but im sure if they put lvl limits on melee gear the outrage would be so huge and it would be withdrawn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 10:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hacking &amp; stuffs</span><hr size=1> it's a good step in the right direction. if it's hackable, then at least the VAST majority of newbies won't be getting kei. it requires both a 60+ enc and hacking, something that most people don't have access too. most newbs just beg or buy kei off of high level enchanetrs:<br>
