><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artillis>Artillis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Enjoys Sheep Erotica</span><br>  Posts: 1874<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 2:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hacking &amp; stuffs</span><hr size=1> I actualy enjoyed the low levels, you want a fun challange start a character from scratch on a different server with no twinking.  I've done it 3 times now.  I started a character on the FV server when it first opened and playing with other people that wern't tweeked out was a nice change you would be supprised how balanced and nice grouping can be in those low levels when people arn't flying through them at 50 levels in a day (slight exageration but there are people that have leveled somewhat close to this with twinking and PLing, heck probably even faster).<br>
<br>
At any rate the only way and I mean only way they will ever get the low end game balanced on older servers is to give everything a level limit.  And I mean a resonable level limit not a lame one like must be level 60 to use a centi long or short sword.  More like level 45 for those two weapons considering the level of mobs and zone they drop in.  FBSS for instance would probably be a level 40 item.  Journey mans boots level 20, Stein of Maggok level 10.<br>
<br>
